menting the TaskChain program have been initiated. The main focus has been on removing duplicate methods and ensuring the code is reviewed and optimized. However, the provided code snippet from `agent2` is incomplete and does not fully address the requirements for the TaskChain program. Below is a summarized and completed version of `solution.py` that includes the basic structure for managing tasks with dependencies.\n\n```json\n{\n  "solution.py": "```python\\n# solution.py\\n\\nclass Task:\\n    def __init__(self, task_id, description, dependencies=None):\\n        self.task_id = task_id\\n        self.description = description\\n        self.dependencies = dependencies if dependencies is not None else []\\n        self.completed = False\\n\\n    def mark_completed(self):\\n        self.completed = True\\n\\n\\nclass TaskChain:\\n    def __init__(self):\\n        self.tasks = {}\\n\\n    def add_task(self, task_id, description, dependencies=None):\\n        if task_id in self.tasks:\\n            raise ValueError(f\'Task with ID {task_id} already exists.\')\\n        self.tasks[task_id] = Task(task_id, description, dependencies)\\n\\n    def get_task_order(self):\\n        visited = set()\\n        order = []\\n\\n        def dfs(task_id):\\n            if task_id in visited:\\n                return\\n            visited.add(task_id)\\n            for dependency in self.tasks[task_id].dependencies:\\n                dfs(dependency)\\n            order.append(task_id)\\n\\n        for task_id in self.tasks:\\n            if task_id not in visited:\\n                dfs(task_id)\\n\\n        return order\\n\\n    def mark_task_completed(self, task_id):\\n        if task_id not in self.tasks:\\n            raise ValueError(f\'Task with ID {task_id} does not exist.\')\\n        self.tasks[task_id].mark_completed()\\n\\n    def is_task_completed(self, task_id):\\n        if task_id not in self.tasks:\\n            raise ValueError(f\'Task with ID {task_id} does not exist.\')\\n        return self.tasks[task_id].completed\\n\\n    def get_task_description(self, task_id):\\n        if task_id not in self.tasks:\\n            raise ValueError(f\'Task with ID {task_id} does not exist.\')\\n        return self.tasks[task_id].description\\n\\n    def get_task_dependencies(self, task_id):\\n        if task_id not in self.tasks:\\n            raise ValueError(f\'Task with ID {task_id} does not exist.\')\\n        return self.tasks[task_id].dependencies\\n\\n# Example usage:\\nif __name__ == \'__main__\':\\n    task_chain = TaskChain()\\n    task_chain.add_task(\'1\', \'Design database schema\')\\n    task_chain.add_task(\'2\', \'Implement database models\', dependencies=[\'1\'])\\n    task_chain.add_task(\'3\', \'Create API endpoints\', dependencies=[\'2\'])\\n    task_chain.add_task(\'4\', \'Write unit tests\', dependencies=[\'3\'])\\n\\n    print(\'Task order:\', task_chain.get_task_order())\\n    task_chain.mark_task_completed(\'1\')\\n    print(\'Is task 1 completed?\', task_chain.is_task_completed(\'1\'))\\n    print(\'Task 2 description:\', task_chain.get_task_description(\'2\'))\\n    print(\'Task 2 dependencies:\', task_chain.get_task_dependencies(\'2\'))\\n```"\n}\n```\n\nThis `solution.py` file includes:\n- A `Task` class to represent individual tasks with attributes for task ID, description, dependencies, and completion status.\n- A `TaskChain` class to manage a collection of tasks, including methods to add tasks, get the order of tasks based on dependencies, mark tasks as completed, check if a task is completed, and retrieve task descriptions and dependencies.\n- Example usage to demonstrate how to use the `TaskChain` class.\n\nThis should serve as a solid foundation for the TaskChain program, and further improvements and optimizations can be made as needed.', 'continue_simulation': True, 'communications': [], 'total_milestones': 0, 'agent_kpis': {}}], 'planning_scores': [-1, -1, -1, -1, -1], 'communication_scores': [-1, -1,